goals.question: What is the trend of deaths over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of Deaths vs Year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if the number of deaths is increasing or decreasing over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of Deaths vs Entity
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which entities have the highest number of deaths and which ones have the lowest.

goals.question: What is the correlation between Deaths and count?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of Deaths vs count
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between the number of deaths and the count.

goals.question: What is the average number of deaths per entity?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of Deaths vs Entity (sorted by average deaths)
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which entities have the highest average number of deaths.

goals.question: What is the percentage change in deaths over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of Percentage change in Deaths vs Year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the rate of change in the number of deaths over the years.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Year'])
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="Entity", y="Deaths", data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='Deaths', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between Deaths and count?', wrap=True)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    avg_deaths = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index().sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=avg_deaths, order=avg_deaths['Entity'])
    chart.axhline(avg_deaths['Deaths'].iloc[0], color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {avg_deaths['Deaths'].iloc[0]:0.2f}")
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title("What is the average number of deaths per entity?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    data['Deaths'] = data['Deaths'].astype(float)
    data['Deaths_pct_change'] = data['Deaths'].pct_change() * 100
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths_pct_change', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['Deaths_pct_change'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}%'.format(data['Deaths_pct_change'].median()))
    chart.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Percentage Change in Deaths')
    chart.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
